AUDIO: 'That\'s what trending actually means. Who is surging right now? That\'s why you\'ll see a repo with 150,000 total stars sitting lower than one with 60,000 because the smaller one'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is growing faster today. Now, one honest warning before we start. Star counts can be gamed. If a brand new repo goes from 0 to 40,000 stars in 3 weeks with almost no'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'issues, no forks, and no real discussion, be skeptical. Real tools leave a trail. So, as we go, watch not just the number, but whether people are actually using'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the thing. With that, let\'s begin. Number 10, Apple/container. Written in Swift, almost 40,000 stars, and it surged onto the list this month. If you\'ve ever run Docker on a Mac, you'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'know it can feel heavy and slow. This is Apple\'s own answer. It runs Linux containers as lightweight virtual machines, built specifically for Apple silicon, so each container boots fast and stays'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out of your way. The honest verdict? It\'s Mac only and it\'s young, but it\'s first party and it\'s real. If you build on a Mac, this is the most'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'exciting container tool in years. Straight from Apple itself. Number nine, DeepSeek Rizonix. This one is written in Go and it\'s a coding agent that lives in'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your terminal. Built specifically around the DeepSeek models. Here\'s the clever part and it\'s our first hint of the pattern. It\'s engineered around prefix cache stability.'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In plain English, it keeps the unchanging part of your conversation in a cache the model can reuse instead of rereading everything from scratch every turn. That means you can leave it running on a long task and it stays cheap.'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The verdict? Niche. Because it\'s tied to DeepSeek. But the idea, don\'t make the model pay for the same context twice, is about to show up again and again.'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Number eight, Last 30 days by M Van Horn. 45,000 stars and it\'s an agent skill. A little folder of instructions you hand your AI.'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
